<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="CH1d0952-en-617ad4db" type="transl"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Lingshujing</title><editor role="translator">Paul Unschuld</editor></titleStmt><publicationStmt><ab>published electronically as part of the TLS project at https://hxwd.org</ab><availability status="4">The copyright status of this work is unclear</availability></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><bibl><title>Lingshujing</title>Berkeley: California University Press, 2016</bibl><ab>Translation of <bibl corresp="#CH1d0952"><title xml:lang="och">靈樞經</title></bibl> into <lang xml:lang="en">English</lang>.</ab></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><creation resp="#CH">Initially created: <date>2024-04-02T11:06:02.595+09:00</date> by CH</creation></profileDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div><head>Translated parts</head><p xml:id="CH1d0952-start"><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:07:51.029+09:00">and they may attach themselvesto the network vessels,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.44" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:07:40.739+09:00">They may attach themselves to the tertiary vessels,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:08:19.624+09:00">they may attach themselves to the conduit vessels,14</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:08:31.159+09:00">they may attach themselves tothe transport vessels,15</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:08:41.134+09:00">they may attach themselves to the deep lying throughway vessels,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.49" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:08:48.516+09:00">they may attachthemselves to the sinews at the spine,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.50" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:09:07.044+09:00">they may attach themselves to the membrane plain of the intestines and the stomach.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.51" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:09:34.574+09:00">Upward16 they tie up with the relaxed sinews.17</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.52" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:09:53.811+09:00">The inundations by evil qi</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.53" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:11:07.007+09:00">areinnumerable.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:12:33.172+09:00">When they have stayed there for some time without being removed,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.39" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:12:48.847+09:00">they will betransmitted further and they will settle outside of the intestines and the stomach,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:12:55.907+09:00">in the membrane plain.12</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:13:10.916+09:00">There they remain for some time and attach themselvesto the vessels.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-2a.42" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:13:12.745+09:00">When they have stayed there for some time without being removed, they rest andaccumulate.13</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:24:29.165+09:00">Huang Di asked Bo Gao:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:24:41.917+09:00">Now,when evil qi settle in a person as visitors,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:40:16.803+09:00">that may cause that person to not being able to close the eyes, and hence not being able to sleep.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:25:24.609+09:00">Which qi cause that?</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:25:37.086+09:00">Bo Gao:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:25:44.14+09:00">The five grains enter the stomach.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:26:29.288+09:00">The dregs, the jin and ye liquids and the stem qi</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:27:01.55+09:00">are separated to enter three channels.1</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:28:18.579+09:00">The fact is:The stem qi collect in the chest,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:28:28.494+09:00">they leave [the chest] through the windpipe.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:28:35.148+09:00">They penetrate the heart vessels,2</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:28:45.28+09:00">and they are responsible for ex- and inhalation.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:30:14.174+09:00">The camp qi</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:30:22.572+09:00">seep out as jin and ye liquids,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:30:31.609+09:00">and they pour into the vessels.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:40:31.152+09:00">There they are transformed to blood,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_071-1a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:30:54.322+09:00">serving to nourish the four limbs.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_072-2a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:41:51.748+09:00">Persons with a harmonious balance of yin and yang [qi],</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_072-2a.42" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:42:00.128+09:00">They live in a peaceful and calm environment.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_072-2a.43" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:42:13.36+09:00">Nothing makes them worry.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_072-2a.44" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:42:23.705+09:00">Nothing causes them to enjoy.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_072-2a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:43:08.586+09:00">They fulfill their tasks</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_072-2a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:44:06.837+09:00">and are always friendly.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_072-2a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:44:19.258+09:00">－</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_072-2a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:44:27.604+09:00">－</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_072-2a.49" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:44:47.907+09:00">－</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_072-2a.50" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:45:52.587+09:00">－</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_075-15a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:49:36.089+09:00">Huang Di:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_075-15a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:49:44.693+09:00">It is possible that one single vessel may generate tens of diseases.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_075-15a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:49:49.491+09:00">That may be pain,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_075-15a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:50:02.716+09:00">that may be an obstruction-illness.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_075-15a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:50:10.616+09:00">That may be heat,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_075-15a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:50:36.444+09:00">that may be cold.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_075-15a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:50:57.354+09:00">that may be a blockage-illness.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_075-15a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:50:52.906+09:00">That may be an itch,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_075-15a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:51:10.116+09:00">Or even a numbness –</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_075-15a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:51:14.228+09:00">the changes are innumerable.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_075-15a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T11:51:38.672+09:00">What is the reason?</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_007-6a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:29:50.071+09:00">The third is called “gate piercing”.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_007-6a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:29:57.282+09:00">&gt;gate piercing:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_007-6a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:30:06.56+09:00">[the needle] is to be pierced straight to the left and right,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_007-6a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:30:19.869+09:00">above the sinew ends,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_007-6a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:30:30.426+09:00">to remove a sinew blockage-illness.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_007-6a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:30:39.105+09:00">This is to bedone cautiously lest blood comes out.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_007-6a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:31:22.65+09:00">This is in correspondence to theheart.&lt;</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_007-6a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:31:34.088+09:00">&gt;an alternative designation is: abyss piercing,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_007-6a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:33:08.221+09:00">or: triumphant piercing.&lt;</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_018-3a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:48:48.758+09:00">Huang Di:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_018-3a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:49:01.204+09:00">When a person has heat [in his body] and ingests beverages and food that movedown into the stomach,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_018-3a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:49:09.704+09:00">and before the qi are stabilized15</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_018-3a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:49:18.797+09:00">this results in sweating,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_018-3a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:49:26.147+09:00">sometimes in the face,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_018-3a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:49:33.203+09:00">sometimes on the back,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_018-3a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:49:42.791+09:00">sometimes involving half of the body,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_018-3a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:50:01.67+09:00">that is, the sweat does not follow the paths of the guard qi and leaves the body,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_018-3a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:50:05.63+09:00">whyis that?</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:56:45.404+09:00">Huang Di asked Shao Yu:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:57:05.256+09:00">I have been informed that the very beginning of all diseases</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:57:17.413+09:00">must be generated bywind, rain, cold and summer heat.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:57:25.272+09:00">They follow the fine body hairs when they enterthe skin structures.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:57:35.006+09:00">In some cases they turn around;</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:57:44.008+09:00">in some cases they remainthere and stay where they are.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:57:53.124+09:00">In some cases this leads to wind with swelling andsweating.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:58:00.183+09:00"> In some cases this leads to melting dan-illness.1</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:58:12.061+09:00">In other cases this resultsin alternating cold and heat sensations.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:58:16.966+09:00">In some cases this leads to locally staticblockage-illness.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T12:58:24.982+09:00">In other cases this leads to accumulations.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T13:56:16.821+09:00">The unusual evil [qi]2that are excessive and spill over,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T13:57:18.615+09:00"> in some cases the disease appearshere,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T13:56:29.772+09:00">they are innumerable.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T13:56:31.271+09:00"> I wish to be informed of the underlying reasons.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T13:57:29.147+09:00">in some cases the disease appears there.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T13:57:44.019+09:00"> I mean, when heaven generatesin humans [the disease] “wind”,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_046-1a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:07:23.44+09:00">why are there such differences?</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.54" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:10:49.62+09:00">Qi Bo replied:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.55" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:12:28.742+09:00">A difficult question, indeed!</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.56" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:12:38.913+09:00">The five long-term depots,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.57" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:12:49.125+09:00">with them [man] correspondsto heaven and earth.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.58" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:12:58.846+09:00">They are associated with [the dynamics of ] yin andyang [qi].</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.59" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:13:10.835+09:00">They correspond to the four seasons</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.60" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:13:19.536+09:00">and they are transformed in accordancewith the five sections [of the five phases].</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.61" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:13:57.841+09:00">Among the five long-term depots</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.62" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:14:12.163+09:00">there are small and big ones, those located above and others located below.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.63" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:15:24.518+09:00">Among the six short-term repositories, too, there are small and big ones,long and short ones, thick and thin ones, curved and straight ones, relaxed and tenseones.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.64" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:15:39.143+09:00">All these 255 are different.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.65" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:15:44.094+09:00">Some are good,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.66" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:16:10.348+09:00">others are malign.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.67" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:16:17.113+09:00">Their signs maybe auspicious or inauspicious.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_047-1a.68" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T14:16:38.222+09:00">I ask for permission to speak about the backgroundof all of this.6</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_050-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T15:27:52.484+09:00">Huang Di asked Shao Yu:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_050-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T15:28:01.928+09:00">There are some people.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_050-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T15:28:13.608+09:00">They walk together, and they stand together.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_050-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T15:28:29.897+09:00">They are of thesame age,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_050-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T15:28:37.857+09:00">and their clothing is identical too.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_050-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T15:28:54.261+09:00">Suddenly they are exposed to a violentwind and to heavy rain.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_050-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T15:29:04.568+09:00">Some of them fall ill.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_050-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T15:29:12.689+09:00">Others do not fall ill.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_050-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T15:29:26.391+09:00">Or, all of themfall ill. Or none of them falls ill.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_050-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T15:30:02.231+09:00">What causes it to be that way?</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_054-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T15:34:45.668+09:00">Huang Di:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_054-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T15:35:03.636+09:00">Longevity and early death are unequally distributed among humans.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_054-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T15:54:54.002+09:00">Some die early, others have a long life.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_054-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:00:24.933+09:00">Some die a sudden death.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_054-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:00:29.51+09:00">Some suffer from a long lasting disease.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_054-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:00:54.142+09:00">I wish to be informed of the underlying WAY.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:06:06.453+09:00">Qi Bo:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:06:16.091+09:00">The qi of the three body sections are all different.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:06:25.813+09:00">They may originate from the yinrealm,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:06:35.057+09:00">and they may originate from the yang realm.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_066-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:06:54.18+09:00">I ask for permission to outlinethe respective norms.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:11:59.007+09:00">Huang Di asked Qi Bo:</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:12:20.318+09:00">I have been informed by you of the nine needles,</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:12:30.266+09:00">and how they are applied to [treatthe] people.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:13:06.611+09:00">However, all the people</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:13:22.815+09:00">have different physical appearances of bloodand qi.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:13:36.439+09:00">It happens that [a patient’s] spirit is excited, and the qi1 move even before a needlehas been applied.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:13:47.074+09:00">It happens that the qi and the needles confront each other.2</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:13:57.297+09:00">It happens that the needle was withdrawn, but the qi flow by themselves.3</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:14:29.341+09:00">It happens that the effect is noticable only after several piercings.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:14:43.476+09:00">It happens that the deployment of the needle causes the qi to move contrary to thenorms.4</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:15:26.382+09:00">It happens that despite repeated piercings the disease increases in its severity.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:15:49.846+09:00">All these six possibilities</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:33:17.911+09:00">[may occur because] everybody’s physical appearance is different.</seg><seg corresp="#CH1d0952_CHANT_067-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-02T16:16:19.934+09:00">I wish to be informed of the underlying rules.</seg></p></div></body></text></TEI>